es, deseeded if preferred","15 g olive oil","800 g unpeeled raw prawns, with heads and shells removed and reserved","1400 g water","40 g rice vinegar","30 g fish sauce","2 whole cloves","1 star anise","3 pinches salt, adjust to taste","3 pinches ground black pepper, adjust to taste","80 g dried Chinese egg noodles","2 pinches wakame flakes              (optional)","100 g fresh bean sprouts","15 fresh coriander leaves"]}],"id":"r156154","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-ODUcU68p--c\/XZMyNPkQl-I\/AAAAAAAAah0\/1NPZy7kosOI45lPwtuTJqdnkaIBXvnetACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6mvrHFG4Un7iAMfL.png","title":"Thai-style prawn broth with spicy apples","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36 g","calories":"1242 kJ \/ 296 kcal"},"usefulItems":"apple-corer, baking paper, large bowl, plate, serving bowl, fine mesh sieve, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Wakame is an edible seaweed that is often used in Japanese, Korean and Chinese cuisines.","If apples are large and prevent closing of Varoma lid, slice off the top portion of the apples.","Replace bean sprouts with thinly sliced fresh mushrooms."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}